Process Steps

Time Frame Selection: Filter for applications updated in the last 10 days
Status Filtering: Select applications with status number 35 ("do not clear credit policy")
Task List Verification: Exclude applications explicitly marked for manual review
Secondary Check Exclusion: Ensure no secondary review indicators are present



Identify potential anomalies in the SIRA auto-clearing process to ensure compliance with credit policy review procedures.
Usage
Run this query daily or as needed to monitor for any applications that may have bypassed manual credit policy review.
Maintenance
Regularly review and update the query criteria to align with any changes in credit policy or application status codes.
